p><strong>Please consider joining our community of people who want to make the world a better place for kids and parents by clicking the box at the bottom of this page to get exclusive tips.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To learn the surprising way Brain Stages came to be, click <a href=\"/blog/too-much-coincidence-not-to-be-part-of-the-cosmic-plan\">here.</a><br/>To find out more about the <em>Brain Stages</em> book, click <a href=\"/book.html\">here.</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Thanks for visiting!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>-Trish Wilkinson</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-0 is-cropped\"></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->', 'About Brain Stages', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '22-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-10-10 20:31:01', '2018-10-10 20:31:01', '', 22, 'http://localhost:8888/2018/10/10/22-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(128, 1, '2018-10-10 20:34:46', '2018-10-10 20:34:46', '<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Raise Smart, Confident Kids and Have Fun Doing It!</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Welcome to Brains Stages, where you can find out the latest research and practical tips for raising and educating children <em><strong>in harmony with how their brains develop</strong></em>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<button style=\"\n			   display: block; \n			   margin: auto; \n			   text-decoration:none; \n			   margin-bottom: 2vh; padding: 5px;\n			   font-family: \'Lato\', sans-serif;\n    color: #545454;\n    font-size: 3vmin;\n			   background-color: #331D6E;\"><a target= \"_blank\" href=\"https://thebrainstages.us15.list-manage.com/subscribe?u=343d8cd6e346b50a86cc67d1b&amp;id=6791140e42\">Get Five Tips To Help Your Kids Ace Tests</a></button>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":33,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":402,\"height\":596} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/brainstagescover-exp4-7d-stroke_1_orig.jpg\" alt=\"Brain Stages Cover\" class=\"wp-image-33\" width=\"402\" height=\"596\"/><figcaption>Brain Stages Cover</figcaption></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You\'ll find answers to questions in accordance with science such as:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>What can you do to give your child a leg up in today’s competitive society while raising a happy, well-adjusted future adult?</li><li>How can you get a disinterested kid engaged in school and learning? (<em>Hint:</em> It\'s probably not what you think.)</li><li>How can you help an anxious child relax for better learning?</li><li>What sure-fire ways can you help a struggling child get caught up in math or reading — and have FUN while you\'re at it?</li><li>How can you get your gifted child\'s needs met?</li><li>What can you do to help kids develop social skills — even if dealing with people isn\'t <em>your</em> best thing?</li><li>What’s the most effective way to empower children for a successful life? (<em>Hint</em>: This is also probably not what you think.) And much more!</li><li><strong>BONUS: You\'ll find your own skills improving and your views more empowering—right along with your kids!</strong></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-2 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/jackie_headshot-2.jpeg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"107\" data-link=\"http://localhost:8888/about-brain-stages-brain-stages/jackie_headshot-3/\" class=\"wp-image-107\"/><figcaption>Jackie Frischknecht, PhD</figcaption></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/trish_headshot-1.jpeg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"108\" data-link=\"http://localhost:8888/about-brain-stages-brain-stages/trish_headshot-2/\" class=\"wp-image-108\"/><figcaption>Trish Wilkinson, Author and Licensed Educator<br/></figcaption></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Jacqueline Frischknecht, PhD and mother of three, and I, Trish Wilkinson, mother of two and veteran teacher, are excited to share with you what we’ve learned through thousands of hours of experience and ongoing research. On the <a href=\"/blog.html\">Brain Stages blog</a>, you\'ll find out how brains work, practical ways to enjoy kids more and stress less, and how to optimize situations as well as solve problems.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Even Better, <strong><em>Bra</em><em>in Stages: How to Raise Smart, Confident Kids and Have Fun Doing It, K – 5</em></strong>, our grade-by-grade guide through the elementary school years, will be available November 13, 2018 to make your life with kids a lot easier and way more pleasant!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Please consider joining our community of people who want to make the world a better place for kids and parents by clicking the box at the bottom of this page to get exclusive tips.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To learn the surprising way Brain Stages came to be, click <a href=\"/blog/too-much-coincidence-not-to-be-part-of-the-cosmic-plan\">here.</a><br/>To find out more about the <em>Brain Stages</em> book, click <a href=\"/book.html\">here.</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Thanks for visiting!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>-Trish Wilkinson</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-0 is-cropped\"></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->', 'About Brain Stages', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '22-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-10-10 20:34:46', '2018-10-10 20:34:46', '', 22, 'http://localhost:8888/2018/10/10/22-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(129, 1, '2018-10-10 20:36:04', '2018-10-10 20:36:04', '<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Raise Smart, Confident Kids and Have Fun Doing It!</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Welcome to Brains Stages, where you can find out the latest research and practical tips for raising and educating children <em><strong>in harmony with how their brains develop</strong></em>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<button style=\"\n			   display: block; \n			   margin: auto; \n			   text-decoration:none; \n			   margin-bottom: 2vh; padding: 5px;\n			   font-family: \'Lato\', sans-serif;\n    			color: #545454;\n    			font-size: 3vmin;\n			   background-color: #331D6E;\">\n	<a style=\"color:white;\" target= \"_blank\" href=\"https://thebrainstages.us15.list-manage.com/subscribe?u=343d8cd6e346b50a86cc67d1b&amp;id=6791140e42\">Get Five Tips To Help Your Kids Ace Tests</a></button>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":33,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":402,\"height\":596} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/brainstagescover-exp4-7d-stroke_1_orig.jpg\" alt=\"Brain Stages Cover\" class=\"wp-image-33\" width=\"402\" height=\"596\"/><figcaption>Brain Stages Cover</figcaption></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You\'ll find answers to questions in accordance with science such as:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>What can you do to give your child a leg up in today’s competitive society while raising a happy, well-adjusted future adult?</li><li>How can you get a disinterested kid engaged in school and learning? (<em>Hint:</em> It\'s probably not what you think.)</li><li>How can you help an anxious child relax for better learning?</li><li>What sure-fire ways can you help a struggling child get caught up in math or reading — and have FUN while you\'re at it?</li><li>How can you get your gifted child\'s needs met?</li><li>What can you do to help kids develop social skills — even if dealing with people isn\'t <em>your</em> best thing?</li><li>What’s the most effective way to empower children for a successful life? (<em>Hint</em>: This is also probably not what you think.) And much more!</li><li><strong>BONUS: You\'ll find your own skills improving and your views more empowering—right along with your kids!</strong></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-2 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/jackie_headshot-2.jpeg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"107\" data-link=\"http://localhost:8888/about-brain-stages-brain-stages/jackie_headshot-3/\" class=\"wp-image-107\"/><figcaption>Jackie Frischknecht, PhD</figcaption></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/trish_headshot-1.jpeg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"108\" data-link=\"http://localhost:8888/about-brain-stages-brain-stages/trish_headshot-2/\" class=\"wp-image-108\"/><figcaption>Trish Wilkinson, Author and Licensed Educator<br/></figcaption></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Jacqueline Frischknecht, PhD and mother of three, and I, Trish Wilkinson, mother of two and veteran teacher, are excited to share with you what we’ve learned through thousands of hours of experience and ongoing research. On the <a href=\"/blog.html\">Brain Stages blog</a>, you\'ll find out how brains work, practical ways to enjoy kids more and stress less, and how to optimize situations as well as solve problems.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Even Better, <strong><em>Bra</em><em>in Stages: How to Raise Smart, Confident Kids and Have Fun Doing It, K – 5</em></strong>, our grade-by-grade guide through the elementary school years, will be available November 13, 2018 to make your life with kids a lot easier and way more pleasant!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Please consider joining our community of people who want to make the world a better place for kids and parents by clicking the box at the bottom of this page to get exclusive tips.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To learn the surprising way Brain Stages came to be, click <a href=\"/blog/too-much-coincidence-not-to-be-part-of-the-cosmic-plan\">here.</a><br/>To find out more about the <em>Brain Stages</em> book, click <a href=\"/book.html\">here.</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Thanks for visiting!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>-Trish Wilkinson</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-0 is-cropped\"></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->', 'About Brain Stages', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '22-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-10-10 20:36:04', '2018-10-10 20:36:04', '', 22, 'http://localhost:8888/2018/10/10/22-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(130, 1, '2018-10-10 20:38:24', '2018-10-10 20:38:24', '<h2 class=\"wsite-content-title\"><em><span style=\"font-size: xx-large;\">Brain Stages</span></em>\n<span style=\"color: #515151; font-size: medium;\"><em><strong>How to Raise Smart, Confident Kids and Have Fun Doing It, K–5</strong></em></span></h2>\n<div>\n<div style=\"height: 0px; overflow: hidden; width: 100%;\"></div>\n\n<hr class=\"styled-hr\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n\n<div style=\"height: 20px; overflow: hidden; width: 100%;\"></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"paragraph\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n\nWho says kids don’t come with instructions?\n\nWe’re pleased to announce the first edition of&nbsp;<em>Brain Stages</em>, a comprehensive grade-by-grade guide through the elementary school years.\n\n​Written in a friendly, conversational style,&nbsp;this book gives you useful tools to boost your kids’ brainpower and help them develop social skills, laying the foundation for&nbsp;them to&nbsp;become&nbsp;happy, successful adults.\n\nBacked by research and experience and filled with fun games, insider information, and amazing life hacks for raising kids,&nbsp;<em>Brain Stages</em> invites parents and caregivers to enjoy kids more&nbsp;and&nbsp;stress less&nbsp;while&nbsp;bringing up well-adjusted humans.\n\n“Finally, a guide to help your child enjoy learning based upon the latest brain research and explained by a veteran teacher, who offers parents fun, practical strategies.”\n— <strong>S. Craddu</strong><strong>ck, Licensed Educational Psychologist</strong>​\n\n</div>', 'The Brain Stages Book', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '20-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-10-10 20:38:24', '2018-10-10 20:38:24', '', 20, 'http://localhost:8888/2018/10/10/20-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(131, 1, '2018-10-10 20:38:59', '2018-10-10 20:38:59', '<h2 class=\"wsite-content-title\"><em><span style=\"font-size: xx-large;\">Brain Stages</span></em><br /><span style=\"color: #515151; font-size: medium;\"><em><strong>How to Raise Smart, Confident Kids and Have Fun Doing It, K–5</strong></em></span></h2>\n<div>\n<div style=\"height: 0px; overflow: hidden; width: 100%;\"> </div>\n<hr class=\"styled-hr\" style=\"width: 100%;\" />\n<div style=\"height: 20px; overflow: hidden; width: 100%;\"> </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"paragraph\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<p>Who says kids don’t come with instructions?</p>\n<p>We’re pleased to announce the first edition of <em>Brain Stages</em>, a comprehensive grade-by-grade guide through the elementary school years.</p>\n<p>​Written in a friendly, conversational style, this book gives you useful tools to boost your kids’ brainpower and help them develop social skills, laying the foundation for them to become happy, successful adults.</p>\n<p>Backed by research and experience and filled with fun games, insider information, and amazing life hacks for raising kids, <em>Brain Stages</em> invites parents and caregivers to enjoy kids more and stress less while bringing up well-adjusted humans.</p>\n<p>“Finally, a guide to help your child enjoy learning based upon the latest brain research and explained by a veteran teacher, who offers parents fun, practical strategies.”<br />— <strong>S. Craddu</strong><strong>ck, Licensed Educational Psychologist</strong>​</p>\n</div>\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":33} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/brainstagescover-exp4-7d-stroke_1_orig.jpg\" alt=\"Brain Stages Cover\" class=\"wp-image-33\"/><figcaption>Brain Stages Cover</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->', 'The Brain Stages Book', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '20-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-10-10 20:38:59', '2018-10-10 20:38:59', '', 20, 'http://localhost:8888/2018/10/10/20-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(133, 1, '2018-10-10 20:39:44', '2018-10-10 20:39:44', '<h2 class=\"wsite-content-title\"><em><span style=\"font-size: xx-large;\">Brain Stages</span></em><br /><span style=\"color: #515151; font-size: medium;\"><em><strong>How to Raise Smart, Confident Kids and Have Fun Doing It, K–5</strong></em></span></h2>\n<div>\n<div style=\"height: 20px; overflow: hidden; width: 100%;\"> </div>\n</div>\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":33} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/brainstagescover-exp4-7d-stroke_1_orig.jpg\" alt=\"Brain Stages Cover\" class=\"wp-image-33\"/><figcaption>Brain Stages Cover</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Who says kids don’t come with instructions?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We’re pleased to announce the first edition of <em>Brain Stages</em>, a comprehensive grade-by-grade guide through the elementary school years.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>​Written in a friendly, conversational style, this book gives you useful tools to boost your kids’ brainpower and help them develop social skills, laying the foundation for them to become happy, successful adults.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Backed by research and experience and filled with fun games, insider information, and amazing life hacks for raising kids, <em>Brain Stages</em> invites parents and caregivers to enjoy kids more and stress less while bringing up well-adjusted humans.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“Finally, a guide to help your child enjoy learning based upon the latest brain research and explained by a veteran teacher, who offers parents fun, practical strategies.”<br/>— <strong>S. Craddu</strong><strong>ck, Licensed Educational Psychologist</strong>​</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'The Brain Stages Book', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '20-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-10-10 20:39:44', '2018-10-10 20:39:44', '', 20, 'http://localhost:8888/2018/10/10/20-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(134, 1, '2018-10-10 20:39:47', '2018-10-10 20:39:47', '<h2 class=\"wsite-content-title\"><em><span style=\"font-size: xx-large;\">Brain Stages</span></em><br /><span style=\"color: #515151; font-size: medium;\"><em><strong>How to Raise Smart, Confident Kids and Have Fun Doing It, K–5</strong></em></span></h2>\n<div>\n<div style=\"height: 20px; overflow: hidden; width: 100%;\"> </div>\n</div>\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":33,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/brainstagescover-exp4-7d-stroke_1_orig.jpg\" alt=\"Brain Stages Cover\" class=\"wp-image-33\"/><figcaption>Brain Stages Cover</figcaption></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Who says kids don’t come with instructions?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We’re pleased to announce the first edition of <em>Brain Stages</em>, a comprehensive grade-by-grade guide through the elementary school years.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>​Written in a friendly, conversational style, this book gives you useful tools to boost your kids’ brainpower and help them develop social skills, laying the foundation for them to become happy, successful adults.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Backed by research and experience and filled with fun games, insider information, and amazing life hacks for raising kids, <em>Brain Stages</em> invites parents and caregivers to enjoy kids more and stress less while bringing up well-adjusted humans.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“Finally, a guide to help your child enjoy learning based upon the latest brain research and explained by a veteran teacher, who offers parents fun, practical strategies.”<br/>— <strong>S. Craddu</strong><strong>ck, Licensed Educational Psychologist</strong>​</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'The Brain Stages Book', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'clos